{
  "stem": "16930.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my-- my-- where we lived, we lived right next to the haberdashery store owned by my uncle.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And next to the haberdashery store was what they called a [NON-ENGLISH], a place where they sold-- where my grandmother had a store, like a-- it was like a cafe where they sold wine, different kinds of wine.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And people just sat there on tables and chairs and they drank wine.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so that was next to that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my father was-- I think my uncle may have already left for the United States, but I know he wasn't there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But my father was helping my grandmother take the things from her store from her store into the basement, because they were looting and things like that.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he was doing that, up and down, carrying things to the basement.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then some police, German Austrian police came to arrest my father.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there were a lot of Austrian people standing around.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Some of them I knew, had known us all the time, neighbors, and some I didn't.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they took my father, the police, while he was doing this, just off the street.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and-- I I ran to my father that I can I go with you?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he said, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Germans-- the Austrians standing around thought it was very funny and they were laughing.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They found this whole scene very funny, or they got a little bit what they call in German there's a word called schadenfreude, pleasure from other people's pain, that means to be an enormous pleasure which people find when others are having-- are troubled or having pain.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And maybe for two reasons, to see other people get it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And certainly at the other hand, it shows them that they are not getting it.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
